ending on the orbital inclination),\nor to stellar pulsations. The latter possibility is made likely by the fact\nthat similar low-amplitude velocity variations, with periods close to 1 yr,\nhave been reported for other CEMP stars in a companion paper (Jorissen et al.,\n2015). A definite conclusion about the origin of the 384 d velocity variations\nshould however await the detection of synchronous low-amplitude photometric\nvariations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Oct 2015 20:16:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-17"}
